---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
import AudioPlayer from '../components/AudioPlayer.astro';
import HighlightBox from '../components/HighlightBox.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = "The home of the pioneering macaw Arielle";
const description = "A macaw called Arielle is the world's most communicative nonhuman animal.";

const events = [
  {
    who: "Mike",
    when: "14 July 2019",
    where: "Clearwater Library, FL",
    what: "Meet the Author"
  },
  {
    who: "Mike",
    when: "27-30 June 2012",
    where: "Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain",
    what: "Disrupted Dialogue: A Macaw Learning Language"
  },
  {
    who: "Mike",
    when: "25-26 August 2012",
    where: "Gateway Parrot Club, St. Louis",
    what: "Beyond Polly Wants a Cracker"
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Navigation slot="navigation" currentPage="home" />
  
  <article>
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>ParrotSpeech.org</h1>
      <h2>The home of the pioneering talking macaw called Arielle</h2>
    </header>

    <AudioPlayer 
      src="/TrackD211T29_BB.wav" 
      caption="Arielle speaking"
      autoplay={false}
    />

    <section class="intro">
      <p class="lead">
        Welcome to the world of Arielle, a Blue and Gold macaw who demonstrates remarkable 
        cognitive speech abilities. Arielle doesn't just mimicâ€”she understands and speaks 
        thoughtfully using English words, phrases, and sentences.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="events-section">
      <h2>Events and Appearances</h2>
      <table class="events-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Who</th>
            <th>When</th>
            <th>Where</th>
            <th>What</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {events.map((event) => (
            <tr>
              <td>{event.who}</td>
              <td>{event.when}</td>
              <td>{event.where}</td>
              <td>{event.what}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="speech-sample">
      <h2>Hear Arielle Speak</h2>
      
      <HighlightBox>
        <p>
          Arielle often assembles series of untutored statements. In this example she makes a
          pronoun substitution that shows a small portion of her understanding of English.
        </p>
      </HighlightBox>

      <AudioPlayer 
        src="/sounds/I_m_a_pretty_girl2.wav" 
        caption="Arielle saying: I'm a pretty, pretty girl!"
      />

      <HighlightBox label="Transcription:">
        <p>
          <strong>Arielle said spontaneously: I'm a pretty, pretty girl!</strong> (followed by kisses)
        </p>
        <p>
          The significance of her statement exceeds the simplicity of the words she speaks. Arielle is 
          substituting pronouns in her speech. She was told "Arielle is a pretty girl" and "You are a pretty girl" 
          but here she voluntarily inserts "I" as the subject to refer to herself.
        </p>
        <p>
          Beyond the pronoun substitution, she correctly conjugates the verb to match the subject, 
          "I am," which she correctly contracts to "I'm." Neither of these phrases were modeled for her.
        </p>
      </HighlightBox>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: #663300;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .page-header h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    color: #663300;
    font-weight: normal;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: #333;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 30px;
  }

  .intro {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px;
  }

  .events-section {
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .events-section h2 {
    color: #FF0000;
  }

  .speech-sample {
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .speech-sample h2 {
    color: #663300;
  }
</style>
